sample.Persons

Class PhysicalPerson

  • java.lang.Object
    • sample.Persons.PhysicalPerson
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, NaturalPerson

    public class PhysicalPerson
extends java.lang.Object
implements NaturalPerson, java.io.Serializable
    It is a class which represents a user - natural person.
    It contains some common information like Name, Surname, Age, BirthYear, PassNumber, Gender, Location and IdentificationCode.
    It also has all essential information about the user, on which all the taxes are based, and its taxes.
    And as it's an application, the class contains also user's login and password for access control.
    See Also:

      • SetAdditionalInf

        public void SetAdditionalInf(double carPrice,
                             int carAge,
                             java.lang.String typeofRealty,
                             double sdquareofRealty,
                             double landSquare)
        This method is made to set an additional information, on which almost all the taxes of the user are based on.
        Parameters:
        carPrice - is a field which keeps information about how much user's car cost (for luxuryTax).
        carAge - is a field which keeps information about how old user's car is (for luxuryTax).
        typeofRealty - is a field which keeps information about user's realty: it can be "flat" or "house" (for realtyTax).
        sdquareofRealty - is a field which keeps information about square of user's realty (for realtyTax).
        landSquare - is a field which keeps information about additional land, if there is no, than landSquare=0 (for landTax).
